column11:
  We define a class of morphisms between strict $\omega$-categories called
discrete Conduch{\'e} $\omega$-functors that generalize discrete Conduch{\'e}
functors between 1-categories and we study their properties related to
polygraphs. The main result we prove is that for every discrete Conduch{\'e}
$\omega$-functor, if its target is a free strict $\omega$-category on a
polygraph then so is its source.
